<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-112-187 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 986 796</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  July 1 1991 v221 n1 p9(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Illinois Bell says there's no place like home - to work. (servicesfor telecommuters and individuals with home-based businesses)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lindstrom, Ann H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Illinois Bell is offering its services to individuals withhome-based businesses and telecommuters through its Work-At-HomePlanning Center in Chicago, IL.andP;  The center provides assistance topeople who are working at home and allows customers to access its12 Work-At-Home service representatives, who are available between8:30 a.m.andP;  and 5:00 p.m.andP;  The center's services include automaticcallback, paging services and telephone bill payment.andP;  It alsooffers hands-on demonstrations of modems, facsimile machines andanswering machines.andP;  Illinois Bell is targeting individuals whowork at home, but it plans to enter the corporate telecommutingmarket in 1992.andP;  The telephone company also provides customerswith a newsletter, a guide and a team of trained specialists.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Illinois Bell Telephone Co. (Services).andO;Topic:     Telecommunications ServicesCustomer RelationsTelephone companiesHome-based businessesTelecommuting.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>